metaInfos.description:
Calculate the dipole transition matrix element. 
 On the following lines, the number of transitions and the involved orbitals are given. Example:  {\tt \begin{tabular}{ccc} \multicolumn{2}{l}{\bf TRANSITION MOMENT} 2 &   6 & 7 6 & 8 \end{tabular} } 
 This calculates the dipole transition matrix elements between KS states 6 and 7, and between 6 and 8.
